    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1344"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1344">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/110.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Alger</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mazatlan</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 9, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your instructions of December 18.<note n="111" xml:id="d1344fn111">
                        <ref target="frus1913#pg_908">For. Rel. 1913, p. 908</ref>. It reads: “You
                        are instructed to extend all possible and proper protection to the lives and
                        properties of Spanish subjects in your district * * *. This also applies to
                        all other foreign subjects within your district.”</note> Request
                    interpretation as meaning of “all proper protection to property of
                    foreigners.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alger</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
